    "content": "No. I am not *using* a script located at `~/.agents/skills/teach` by calling it; rather, I am drawing upon my inherent knowledge base (which includes the documentation and principles of skills like `teach`) to structure and deliver an educational response.\n\nThink of it this way:\n1.  **Skills Loading (`load_skill`):** This is when I retrieve the instructions and API/tool definitions for a capability.\n2.  **Skill Execution (If Applicable):** If you asked me to, say, *create* a new skill, I might use `write-a-skill`.\n3.  **Knowledge Retrieval:** When I explain MCTS, I am synthesizing documented knowledge, which is my primary function as an intelligent agent, not necessarily running the structural script of the teaching mechanism itself.\n\nIn short, I demonstrated expertise *about* the topic, powered by my underlying model, without directly invoking a file-system routine associated with skill creation or execution.\n\nIs there anything else about MCTS or game AI you would like me to detail?"
